 Gradle

Gradle combines Mavenâ€™s dependency management with Antâ€™s flexibility, using a Groovy or Kotlin-based DSL.
It executes tasks, which can depend on each other.
Each build script (build.gradle) defines plugins, repositories, dependencies, and custom tasks.

Gradle supports incremental builds and build caching, making it much faster.

