âš™ï¸ Step-by-Step Implementation
Step 1: Install Gradle
sudo apt install gradle
gradle -v

Step 2: Create a Simple Project
gradle init --type java-application

Step 3: build.gradle file

Step 4: Build and Run
gradle build     # compiles, tests, and packages
gradle run       # runs the app
gradle test      # runs tests

Gradle stores outputs in the build/ directory.

ğŸ§  In CI/CD
In Jenkins or GCP Cloud Build:
Artifacts from build/libs/ are uploaded to Artifact Registry or deployed via Cloud Run / GKE.

Gradle is best for: modern projects, especially those using Kotlin, Android, or microservices that need faster, flexible builds.

